The mystery of the aura in Norway is solved: the Russians were testing a rocket
A strange luminous phenomenon of unknown origin was observed over Norway.
The Russian Defense Ministry only yesterday acknowledged testing an intercontinental ballistic rocket not far from Norway's borders.
The launch was still a failure, however, and the "Bulava" missile, which was originally supposed to be the pride of the Russian army, is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Its repeated presence during the rocket tests did not have the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Most of the time, either Bulava did not fly away, or it was damaged in mid-flight.
Russian newspapers speak of "Bulava" as the "missile that does not fly"
A missile that doesn't fly but shines
