It was obviously the engine of the third stage of the rocket that exploded.
This time, "Bulava" flew from the nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij that was sailing below the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and submerged
This is why the mysterious light over Norway caused by a precisely unidentified flying object was likely caused by a faulty "Bulava".
Moreover, the Norwegians did not doubt for a moment that it was a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot absolutely speak of failure.
The first two stages of the rocket resisted and the damage only hit the third.
