Strong mobilization in Copenhagen and around the world for the climate
Tens of thousands of people demonstrated Saturday to demand an ambitious and binding agreement on the fight against global warming, around the world and in Copenhagen, where police made several hundred arrests.
At least thirty thousand people, according to the police, a hundred thousand according to the organizers, marched in the cold in the Danish capital, on the sidelines of the United Nations Climate Conference, responsible for reaching by Friday an agreement that could enter into force on January 1, 2013.
For Connie Hedegaard, Danish president of the climate conference, the growing mobilization on climate around the world, illustrated by these demonstrations, has contributed to make "the political price" of a failure in Copenhagen very high.
