History-geo emerges strengthened from the reform of the general high school, according to Chatel
National Education Minister Luc Chatel said in an interview to be published in the JDD on Sunday that history and geography were "strengthened" from the reform of the general high school, despite the abolition of their compulsory education in scientific terminal.
Now, first-year students will all have four hours a week and the same program for a shared common culture, says Chatel.
For the minister, "we must get out of hypocrisy" because, according to him, "the S stream is no longer a scientific sector" but "basically, it concentrates the best students".
