Late payments: anger of prison guards, planned actions
The unions of prison guards on Friday called for a "general mobilization" to demand the payment by the end of the year holidays of bonuses and overtime whose payment has been postponed to January for budgetary reasons.
FO-penitentiary (2nd union of guards) asked staff who will not be on duty to demonstrate Tuesday morning in front of the prisons and to "block" them, to "denounce the theft of their dues".
