Cuba: hundreds of supporters of the government shouting at the "Ladies in White"
A few hundred supporters of the Cuban government on Thursday shouted at the wives of political detainees gathered in Havana for World Human Rights Day, and prevented another demonstration for which a dozen dissidents were arrested.
Forty "Ladies in White", wives or relatives of political prisoners, were booed in the street by supporters of Raul Castro's government as they marched to the center of the capital to demand the release of political prisoners, an AFP journalist found.
Down with the Yankees!, "mercenaries!", "the street belongs to the revolutionaries!", "Long live Fidel and Raul!" chanted, fist raised, the supporters of power to the dissidents.
