And this even if three employers' organizations (FNTR, Unostra, OTRE) had slammed the door.
But it took more than six hours of a meeting that started at 11:00 for everyone to agree and for the text to be signed by 18:00.
The conflict "would have been very damaging for businesses" and "it was feared that it would disrupt the holiday season," Bussereau said.
The text provides for a wage increase of 4% for the lowest wages (in local and regional road transport) and 2.9% for the highest (international transport).
In hourly rates, for low wages, "we go from 8.72 euros to 9.06.
