Mr. Bussereau recalled that "a decrease of 100 million euros in employers' contributions" was the subject of a government amendment to the draft amending finance law for 2009, voted on the night of Thursday to Friday by the National Assembly.
The government will ask the Senate to vote it "in identical terms".
The signing of TLF allows the agreement to apply initially to companies that are members of this organization, and secondly, to the entire profession, in the event of an extension by the Minister of Labour.
It will be done "as soon as possible," Bussereau said.
Opposition from employers' organisations can only delay the process.
The FNTR denounced a "fool's bargain", because the 100 million euros "had already been promised to the sector to offset part of the carbon tax".
The Secretary of State for Transport forced us to negotiate urgently, not at the conclusion of a shared analysis, but so as not to upset the turkey eaters of the next New Year's Eve, lamented Unostra.
For Otre, the agreement risks "digging the grave of a very large number of SMEs in the sector in the next 12 months".
