The evacuation represents an "unacceptable infringement" on freedom of research and teaching.
Focusing attention exclusively on acts of vandalism only serves to "delegitimize and criminalize the protest" and tries to obscure the reasons for the mobilization.
The University's Steering Committee has thus withdrawn from the debates that would be essential.
The lecturers demand that criminal proceedings be immediately suspended.
The majority of occupants did not take part in the damage.
Legitimization of protests
The young people of the Verdi service sector and the German Trade Union Confederation (DGB) show solidarity with the students.
The protests are just a legitimate expression of growing concern for our own future, says Alexander Klein, regional youth secretary of the Verdi union.
As for the Minister of Science of the Land of Hesse Eva Kühne-Hörmann (CDU), she took up the cause of the action taken by the President of the University and the police.
We thank the President of the University.
