Pending the presentation of their offers next May, the planned investment amounts to 1,700 million Australian dollars (about 1,047 million euros) and in the last phase three consortia are competing with each other, with a notable presence of European manufacturers.
The group called Transcity is led by Acciona, the only Spanish company in the lisse, and its partners are BMD and Ghella.
